org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser.restful.server

Class KeyedDiffusiveStrategyRepository

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser.restful.server.KeyedDiffusiveStrategyRepository

  • public class KeyedDiffusiveStrategyRepository
extends java.lang.Object
    Keyed repository hold information about how to diffuser tasks (strategy and load threshold) The KeyedDiffusiveStrategyRepository.SharedRegistry is the shared registry, but others can be created with different keys as needed.
    Author:
    Robert Philipp

    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static KeyedDiffusiveStrategyRepository getInstance()
        Returns:
        the shared instance of the diffusive strategy repository. Sets the DiffuserStrategy to the DEFAULT_STRATEGY (RandomDiffuserStrategy), and the load threshold to the DEFAULT_LOAD_THRESHOLD = 0.7.
        See Also:
        setLoadThreshold(double), setStrategy(DiffuserStrategy), setValues(DiffuserStrategy, double)

      • getInstance

        public static KeyedDiffusiveStrategyRepository getInstance(java.lang.Object key)
        Returns the named instance if the key exists, or a new object with the key name if the key doesn't already exist. Sets the DiffuserStrategy to the DEFAULT_STRATEGY (RandomDiffuserStrategy), and the load threshold to the DEFAULT_LOAD_THRESHOLD = 0.7.
        Parameters:
        key - The key associated, or to be associated, with the registry instance
        Returns:
        the named instance if the key exists, or a new object if the key doesn't exist
        See Also:
        setLoadThreshold(double), setStrategy(DiffuserStrategy), setValues(DiffuserStrategy, double)

      • associate

        public static KeyedDiffusiveStrategyRepository associate(java.lang.Object key,
                                         java.lang.Object newKey)
        Associates the specified new key to the registry that is currently associated with the specified key. In other words, associates the specified new key to the same registry as the key (if the key exists). As as side effect, any previous associations the new key may have are over written.
        Parameters:
        key - The key that holds the current association to the registry
        newKey - The object to associate to the same registry as the key.
        Returns:
        the keyed registry associated with specified new key if it is being replaced; or null if it is not being replaced
